title: Greenland Trading Corp. Recalls Squab Products Produced Without Benefit of Import Inspection
summary: WASHINGTON, July 30, 2015 Greenland Trading Corp., a Paterson, N.J., establishment, is recalling approximately 12,672 pounds of squab (domesticated pigeon) produced in France that were not presented at the U.S. point of entry for inspection, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service...
